# vsock_test test IDs to skip in the default Linux<->Windows interop suite.
#
# Format: <id>  # reason
#   - <id>     numeric test ID as printed by `vsock_test --list`
#   - reason   free-form short text after `#`
#
# Consumed by the viosock-vsock-test skill: when present, its IDs are added to
# `--skip` on both sides of the run. Explicit `--pick N` from the caller bypasses.
# Longer notes for individual tests belong in test-notes.md next to this file.

3   # SOCK_STREAM server close: WSAPoll FD_CLOSE / WSP IOCTL 10043 (WSAEPROTONOSUPPORT); desyncs control channel
8   # SOCK_SEQPACKET timeout - SEQPACKET semantic mismatch on Windows AF_VSOCK
9   # SOCK_SEQPACKET invalid receive buffer - SEQPACKET error path differs
10  # SOCK_STREAM poll() + SO_RCVLOWAT - SO_RCVLOWAT not honoured / poll semantics
11  # SOCK_SEQPACKET big message - SEQPACKET large-msg path
12  # SOCK_STREAM test invalid buffer - invalid-buffer error mapping differs
13  # SOCK_SEQPACKET test invalid buffer - SEQPACKET invalid-buffer path
15  # SOCK_SEQPACKET MSG_PEEK - SEQPACKET MSG_PEEK semantics
22  # SOCK_STREAM virtio credit update + SO_RCVLOWAT - Linux-internal virtio credit mechanics
23  # SOCK_STREAM virtio credit update + low rx_bytes - ditto
25  # SOCK_SEQPACKET ioctl(SIOCOUTQ) - SIOCOUTQ on SEQPACKET
35  # SOCK_SEQPACKET ioctl(SIOCINQ) - SIOCINQ on SEQPACKET
38  # SOCK_STREAM TX credit bounds - virtio TX credit edge case
